ge Bricks of HQ Ore:  88<br>Enchanted Gold Bars:  13<br>Flasks of Water:  63<br>Rain Water (foraged):  13<br>Griffene Blood:  13<br>Essence of Sunlight:  26<br>Leather Padding:  13<br><br>Now - this stuff trivials at skill values greater than 206, so we need to know the skill of the smith you plan on using to determine a fizzle rate.<br><br>However, assuming 1/4 to 1/6 success rates would be safe at this point.  For the sake of arguement, let's use 1/5.  Also we need to assume compounding effects of combines.  This gets difficult.<br><br>That means to assure the build of a full suit, we'll need 400-500 Large Bricks of HQ ore; 52+ ea of Leather Padding, Griffene Blood, Rain Water, and Enchanted Gold Bars, 104 Essences of Sunlight.  This is going to be a  big order to fill <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br><br>My suggestion is this:<br><br>(1) Get your human smith contact arranged.<br>(2) Start gathering components.<br>(3) when we've amassed some small fraction of what we need (enough to build several pieces) we contact an enchanter and get the blocks enchanted and then contact the smith to get the pieces made.  The big thing here is that the blocks are non -stackable.<br>(4) the smith starts making pieces and over the next while we start amassing your armor.<br><br>Now, a note of explanation and warning:  Because of the incredible difficulty in amassing parts for cultural and high end trades-fabricated items, SOE/VI has added a feature to the game which announces the success or failure in fabrication of an item.  Believe it or not, this was added at the request of the tradespeople <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   This was done because of the incredibly high fizzle rates on the high end equipment and they wanted independent verification of failure.  So, please group with the smith/tailor involved, you will know if they succeed or fail and what they succeeded or failed at.  Also, we will need to find someone we trust as these components will sell for a kings ransom (as will the completed armor).<br><br>I hope this helps....<br> <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Forin Ironshield</B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Ariel" SIZE=1>Paladin of Underfoot<BR>Aegis Wolves<BR><BR>Master Smith, Master Fletcher<BR><I>"Animals die, friends die and I shall die.  But one thing never dies...<BR>and that is the reputation we leave behind at our deaths.</I></FONT></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uforin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Forin</A> at: 1/30/02 3:55:17 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003030><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uforin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Forin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br>  Posts: 608<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/30/02 4:11:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=821.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mandilloran - Enchanted Gold Antonian Full Plate Researc</span><hr size=1> Also, a clarification (or rather additional information):<br><br>3 small bricks of ore combine to form 1 large brick of ore (if done by a smith in a forge)<br><br>3 large bricks of ore combine to form 1 block of ore.<br><br>Ore can only be enchanted in the &quot;Large Brick&quot; state.<br><br>The &quot;Enchanted High Quality folded sheets of metal&quot; required to make the armor are made from enchanted Blocks of ore (i.e. 3 enchanted large bricks combined to form a block and then used to make the folded sheet).<br><br>This leads to the incredibly large number of enchanted blocks of HQ ore required.<br><br>The gold bars needed to make the armor will have to be enchanted gold bars. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Forin Ironshield</B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Ariel" SIZE=1>Paladin of Underfoot<BR>Aegis Wolves<BR><BR>Master Smith, Master Fletcher<BR><I>"Animals die, friends die and I shall die.  But one thing never dies...<BR>and that is the reputation we leave behind at our deaths.</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003030><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uforin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Forin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br>  Posts: 609<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/30/02 4:13:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=821.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mandilloran - Enchanted Gold Antonian Full Plate Researc</span><hr size=1> More erratta:<br><br>The enchanted bricks can only be combined to form blocks of ore at the Antonican Forge in Qeynos or the Seafarer's Forge in Freeport by a Human smith.<br><br>Bricks and Blocks are non-stackable <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Forin Ironshield</B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Ariel" SIZE=1>Paladin of Underfoot<BR>Aegis Wolves<BR><BR>Master Smith, Master Fletcher<BR><I>"Animals die, friends die and I shall die.  But one thing never dies...<BR>and that